                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, very deep reddish-brown (partly very bleak).</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; directives to the
                           ministers and their abbreviations; titles of the books to be read;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals. 
                           On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 2r), a few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="band" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: Simple coloured (black, very deep
                        reddish-brown) ornamental band.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="band" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: Simple coloured (black, very deep
                        reddish-brown) ornamental band (wave forms).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="band" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>: Simple coloured (black, very deep
                        reddish-brown) ornamental band (wave forms).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>: <desc type="DonationNote">Donation
                                 note.<quote xml:lang="gez">
                                 <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: ዝመጽሐፈ፡ ጥምቀት፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ አቶ፡ ተማኑ፡ ወስመ፡
                                 ክርስትናሁ፡ ገብረ፡ መድህን፡ ወስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ባሕርየ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለደብረ፡ አቡነ፡ ሊባኖስ፡
                                 ዘአንበሰት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርኃ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</quote>
                              <quote xml:lang="en"/> Written in the main hand. The note mentions the
                              donor, ʾato Tamānu and his baptismal name Gabra Madhǝn. His father
                              Bāḥrǝya Śǝllāse is also mentioned. The note reports also that the Ms.
                              was donated to the church of Dabra ʾAbuna Libānos ʾAnbasat.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word wa-zalǝfani “and also perpetually” is written
                           in the upper margin in <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>.
 - Pen
                           trials in pencil in <locus target="#37v">37v</locus>, 38r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
